<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lively2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lively,</orth> adv. to the life, very naturally: <cit><quote>her griefs, so l. shown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 389" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 389</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>which I so l. acted,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 174</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as l. painted as the deed was done,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 58.</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>the life as l. mocked,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 19</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou counterfeitest most l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 85</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>